# Docstrings: No Escape for Double Quotes

Inside a **triple-quoted** Python string (`"""..."""`), a single double quote
`"` does **not** end the string. Only the sequence `"""` ends it.

Do **not** escape double quotes in docstrings: write `"1"` not `\"1\"`.
Escaping is unnecessary and makes the text harder to read.

## Example

```python
# unnecessary
"""Skipped when DOCSIG_DEBUG is set to \"1\"."""

# correct
"""Skipped when DOCSIG_DEBUG is set to "1"."""
```

This applies only to triple-quoted strings. Inside a single- or double-quoted
string, escaping rules are different.
